{
  "stem": "18102.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't until years later, when I understood what that was and the whole story of it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my father did remember Sugihara's name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had the passport, remember.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His signature was on it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sugihara's signature is on the passport.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Both.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe it to be both.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At least, that's my memory of it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I haven't looked at it in a long time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, not a visa.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What we got was papers that allowed us to leave.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was under Stalin's sort of orders.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was just happy to get rid of refugees.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And anyone that had a visa to-- to go somewhere, like this transit visa to Japan, that applied for permission had a chance.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when you apply for permission, of course you have to fill out all the papers and all the documents.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you have to explain, in fact, where you're from and why you want to leave Russia's good offices.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was dangerous for my father, because if the ministry of, the foreign ministry of Russia, connected up the fact that we weren't really running from the Nazis anymore, that our home was Bialystock, and that in effect my father was running from the Russians, that meant Siberia at best.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so the decision to, whether to apply for permission to leave or not was a decision we made as a family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was taken into that-- those proceedings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Of course, I voted with my parents, who both voted to take the chance and make the application.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
